# Galaxy Map — Task Tracker for AI Agents

## Architecture
- Backend: Python FastAPI + async SQLite (backend/main.py), database: board.db
- Frontend: React 18 + Vite (frontend/src/App.jsx), polls backend every 3s
- MCP Server: FastMCP (mcp-server/), exposes task CRUD as MCP tools
- Config: YAML-based status configuration (backend/config/statuses.yaml)
- No auth, no websockets

## Running
- Backend: cd backend && pip install -r requirements.txt && uvicorn main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
- Frontend: cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev
- Docker: docker compose up (3 containers: backend, frontend, mcp-server)

## Key API Endpoints
- GET/POST /api/tasks — List/create tasks
- PATCH /api/tasks/{id} — Partial update
- POST /api/tasks/{id}/claim — Atomic claim (409 if already claimed)
- PATCH /api/tasks/{id}/metadata — Merge keys into metadata
- GET /api/statuses — Status definitions with allowed transitions

## Conventions
- Status transitions are validated server-side
- Metadata is merged (not replaced) via the metadata endpoint
- Frontend dynamically sizes grid to number of status columns
